# malloc -- custom memory allocator

A minimal implementation of malloc(3), free(3), and
calloc(3) using sbrk(2).

Files:
my_malloc.h -- header, struct defs and prototypes
my_malloc.c -- allocator implementation
main.c -- test driver
Makefile -- build rules

Building:
$ make run

How it works:
Each block is preceded by a header that tracks its
size, free status, and a pointer to the next block.
my_malloc walks the linked list looking for a free
block of sufficient size. If none is found, it extends
the heap with sbrk. my_free marks the block as free.
my_calloc allocates and zeroes memory.

Limitations:

- No block splitting or coalescing
- sbrk is deprecated on modern systems
- Not thread-safe

Author: tacheraSasi
